Blog 1.4.1

	* Additional control links throughout the blog system.
	* New shortcut methods for publishing articles.
	* Switched default article status to draft instead of published.
	* Fixed some minor glitches with the published date if it's still in draft.
	* Minor styling tweaks.
	--Charlie Powell <charlie@eval.bz>  Wed, 20 Feb 2013 16:48:08 -0500

Blog 1.4.0

	* New styles for blogs.
	* New javascript for blogs, infitite scrolling of blog listing pages via waypoint.
	* New view for blogs, /blogs.  This is a complete syndicate of all blogs on the site and
	  their articles.
	* Expanded the admin section of /blogs/admin for super admins.  This now displays the
	  individual articles in a data-friendly view.
	* Added a published date to blog articles.  This date is the date the article is switched
	  from draft to published.
	* Removed the BlogArticleTagModel; this was never implemented.
	* Blog articles now record their own page, but are not selectable via the new selectable
	  option.
	--Charlie Powell <charlie@eval.bz>  Mon, 04 Feb 2013 15:36:01 -0500

Blog 1.3.0

	* Redesigned how the blog articles behave.  They are now registered as their own page, and
	  get all the benefits thereof.
	* Added multiple types of blogs, currently standard and review exist.
	* Implemented new features introduced in 2.4.2
	--Charlie Powell <charlie@eval.bz>  Fri, 01 Feb 2013 20:13:29 -0500

Blog 1.2.1

	* Assigned the page author as the user object, this allows the extended functionality in 2.4.0 to be used and the profile linked in the head.
	* Minor optimizations for machines, (alt tags).
	* Added multisite support.
	-- Charlie Powell <charlie@eval.bz>  30 Dec 2012

